Download Adobe Audition 3.0: http://thepiratebay.org/torrent/3883065/Adobe.Audition.v3.WinAll.Cracked-NoPE
to determine if it is a re-encode of another file. 

Steps:
1. Open audition and click on edit.
2. Drag and Drop (or add) a mp3 file into audition
3. 3. Click on "View" and then Spectral Frequency Display (Shift+F)

A true 320 source will be 20Hz or above..
128 Re-encodes or 192 re-encodes will be stuck @ 16Hz or 18Hz...
